==Background==

Riots on 18 December in [[Sidi Bouzid]] went largely unnoticed, although [[social media]] sites such as ''[[Facebook]]'' and ''[[YouTube]]'' featured images of police dispersing youths who attacked shop windows and damaged cars. One protester, [[Mohamed Bouazizi]], set [[self-immolation|himself alight]] in protest against the confiscation of his fruit and vegetable cart. He was subsequently transferred to a hospital in Tunis where he died on 4 January.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://af.reuters.com/article/topNews/idAFJOE70408420110105 |title=Tunisian who sparked rare protests dies: relatives -Reuters |publisher=Af.reuters.com |date=2011-01-05 |accessdate=2011-01-14}}</ref>
